nodes.summary:
The excerpt defines key timing and synchronization concepts for Ethernet-based streaming in AUTOSAR AP R25-11.  
It introduces:  
- “stream data consumer” (a network end-node that continuously receives stream data, also called a listener);  
- “AVTP presentation time” (the gPTP instant when AVTPDU payload is delivered to the consumer, calculated as current global time plus max transit time, excluding local processing delays);  
- “max transit time” (worst-case network delay from talker to listener used to set the presentation time);  
- “media clock” (a constant-rate hardware clock, e.g. 48 kHz);  
- “media clock provider” (the node that hosts the media clock and multicasts IEEE1722 CRF streams containing presentation timestamps aligned to that clock rate).
